    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-05-26T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-05-26T18:00:00-05:00" n="113"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d113">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">868.01/568: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador to the Greek Government in Exile in Egypt</hi> (<persName
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacVeagh</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-05-26T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 26, 1944—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Greek 77. Please convey the President’s thanks to M. Papandreou for his message
                    transmitted in your Greek 167, May 22, 7 p.m. The President and the American
                    Government and people have learned with the utmost pleasure the good news of the
                    unity agreement reached in Lebanon, which they are confident will help speed the
                    liberation and restoration of Greece.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
